		<title>Top Hezbollah commander killed in Syria</title>


		<description>BEIRUT (Reuters) - Top Hezbollah commander Mustafa Badreddine has been killed in an attack in Syria, the Lebanese Shi'ite group said on Friday, the biggest blow to the Iranian-backed organization since its military chief was killed in 2008.<div class="feedflare">

		<title>Syrian Observatory: air strike kills 16 Nusra militants</title>


		<description>BEIRUT (Reuters) - An air strike hit a Nusra Front meeting in northwestern Syria, killing 16 senior members of the al Qaeda-linked group, the Syrian Observatory for Human Rights said on Friday.<div class="feedflare">

		<title>Turkish military says 15 PKK militants killed in southeast: NTV</title>


		<description>ISTANBUL (Reuters) - Fifteen militants of the outlawed Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) were killed in clashes in Turkey's southeastern Sirnak province, broadcaster NTV reported, citing the Turkish military.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>China, U.S. should manage South China Sea differences constructively: Chinese general</title>


		<description>SHANGHAI (Reuters) - China and the United States should manage their differences over disputed waters in the South China Sea constructively, one of China's top military officials has said.<div class="feedflare">

<item>
		<title>Shooting in northern Iraqi town kills 12 - police, hospital sources</title>


		<description>BAGHDAD (Reuters) - Three gunmen opened fire overnight on a cafe in northern Iraq where young men had gathered at the start of the weekend holiday, killing at least 12 and wounding 25, police and hospital sources said on Friday.<div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=ujXU9MU1uGg:pofjBvI8thI:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=ujXU9MU1uGg:pofjBvI8thI:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=ujXU9MU1uGg:pofjBvI8thI:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=ujXU9MU1uGg:pofjBvI8thI:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=ujXU9MU1uGg:pofjBvI8thI:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>

<item>
		<title>War on Islamist militants tests Tunisia's young democracy</title>


		<description>TUNIS - Four days after Islamist militants shot dead 21 tourists in Tunisia's Bardo museum last year, police rounded up dozens of people suspected of links with the gunmen.<div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=3cu3jxsVqlc:E5qJi1vojK0:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=3cu3jxsVqlc:E5qJi1vojK0:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=3cu3jxsVqlc:E5qJi1vojK0:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=3cu3jxsVqlc:E5qJi1vojK0:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=3cu3jxsVqlc:E5qJi1vojK0:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>

<item>
		<title>U.S. troops stationed at Libya outposts: Washington Post</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - U.S. special operations troops have been stationed at two outposts in Libya since late last year to try to enlist local support for a possible offensive against Islamic State, the Washington Post reported on Thursday, citing U.S. officials.<div class="feedflare">
<a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=zfdiMxHjo_A:zkcMkjoUsp4:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=zfdiMxHjo_A:zkcMkjoUsp4:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=zfdiMxHjo_A:zkcMkjoUsp4:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=zfdiMxHjo_A:zkcMkjoUsp4:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=zfdiMxHjo_A:zkcMkjoUsp4:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>

		<title>Russia tops agenda for White House visit by Nordic leaders</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - The leaders of Sweden, Denmark, Finland, Norway and Iceland will be treated to the pomp of a White House state visit on Friday, a summit where Russia's military aggression will top the agenda.<div class="feedflare">

		<title>Brazil's Temer calls for unity, confidence for Brazil recovery</title>


		<description>BRASILIA (Reuters) - Brazil's interim President Michel Temer called on his country to rally behind his government of "national salvation," hours after the Senate voted to suspend and put on trial his leftist predecessor, Dilma Rousseff, for breaking budget laws.<div class="feedflare">

		<title>Mexico says unhappy with Egypt's response to 2015 attack on tourists</title>
